Shyam Singha Roy is a 2021 Indian Telugu-language period romantic drama film[2] directed by Rahul Sankrityan from a story written by Janga Satyadev. The film stars Nani in a dual role alongside Sai Pallavi, Krithi Shetty and Madonna Sebastian. It is partly set in the backdrop of Kolkata in the 1970s and it is based on the theme of reincarnation.[3]

The film was announced in February 2020 and principal photography took place from December 2020 to July 2021 in Hyderabad and Kolkata. Production and release were delayed due to the COVID-19 pandemic. Shyam Singha Roy was theatrically released on 24 December 2021 and opened to mixed reviews with critics praising the performances while criticizing the screenplay.[4] The film emerged successful at the box office grossing over â‚¹50crore.[5]
